POP EYE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PATRICK GOLDSTEIN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HART OF GOLD: Who's the world's youngest popster? Our money's on <PERSON>Taro Hart</PERSON>, son 
of Grateful Dead drummer <PERSON>Mickey Hart</PERSON>, who is the co-star of <PERSON>Hart</PERSON>'s new album, 
"Music to Be Born By," the perfect gift for your crystal-worshiping New Age 
chums. Due out from <ORGANIZATION>Rykodisc</ORGANIZATION> in <DATE>March</DATE>, the record features Taro's heartbeat in 
the womb accompanied by <PERSON>Hart</PERSON>'s performance on drums, bass and wooden flute. 
According to <PERSON>Hart</PERSON>, the music is designed to provide child-bearing women with a 
"soundscape of comforting patterns to assist in the birthing process." . . . 
Are you ready for a video magazine devoted to (gasp) heavy metal? It's called 
"Hard 'N Heavy," with a premiere hourlong issue devoted to uncensored videos 
from <ORGANIZATION>Ozzy Osbourne</ORGANIZATION> and Anthrax, an <PERSON>Alice Cooper</PERSON> career retrospective, scenes 
from <ORGANIZATION>Motley Crue</ORGANIZATION> mainstay <PERSON>Vince Neil</PERSON>'s feature film debut (in "Police Academy 
VI") and other headbanger highlights. The video, which is due out every two 
months, will retail for <MONEY>$20</MONEY>. . . . <ORGANIZATION>Sandra Bernhard</ORGANIZATION>'s notorious one-woman 
Off-Broadway show, "Without You I'm Nothing," will be immortalized on vinyl in 
<DATE>May</DATE>, thanks to <ORGANIZATION>Enigma Records</ORGANIZATION>. The two-album sound track includes the 
acid-tongued comedienne's renditions of Prince's "Little Red Corvette" and 
<PERSON>Billy Paul</PERSON>'s "Me and <PERSON>Mrs. Jones</PERSON>." Of Enigma, <PERSON>Bernhard</PERSON> said: "It's the home of 
Poison and Stryper, so I couldn't be happier." . . . Speaking of Enigma -- it's 
launching an Enigma Retro label that will feature classic out-of-print releases 
(though only on CD or cassette). The label debuts with very early <PERSON>Alice Cooper</PERSON> 
("Pretties for You"), the <ORGANIZATION>GTO</ORGANIZATION>'s ("Permanent Damage") with releases from <PERSON>Ted 
Nugent</PERSON>, <PERSON>Lord Buckley</PERSON> and <PERSON>Lenny Bruce</PERSON> to follow. 
</P></TEXT>
